Sections.File: src/labs/1. Operational Amplifier/Part A - Operation as Inverting amplifier/0. Creative.cir
Sections.Name: 0. Creative
Sections.Solution:
*
.SUBCKT LT1008 3 2 7 4 6 1 8
* USE C=30 PF IN MAIN CIRCUIT (CA TO CB).
* INPUT
RC1 7 80 8842
RC2 7 90 8842
Q1 80 2 10 QM1
Q2 90 3 11 QM2
DDM1 2 3 DM2
DDM2 3 2 DM2
C1 80 90 8.66e-12
RE1 10 12 224.6
RE2 11 12 224.6
IEE 12 4 6e-6
RE 12 0 33330000
CE 12 0 1.579E-12
* INTERMEDIATE
GCM 0 8 12 0 2.841E-11
GA 8 0 80 90 1.131E-04
R2 8 0 100000
* EXTERNAL COMP CAP USED FOR C2 (SEE NOTE ABOVE).
GB 1 0 8 0 196
* OUTPUT
RO1 1 6 100
RO2 1 0 900
RC 17 0 6.802e-5
GC 0 17 6 0 14700
D1 1 17 DM1
D2 17 1 DM1
D3 6 13 DM2
D4 14 6 DM2
VC 7 13 1.774
VE 14 4 1.774
IP 7 4 0.000374
DSUB 4 7 DM2
.MODEL QM1 NPN(IS=8e-16 BF=66670)
.MODEL QM2 NPN(IS=8.009E-16 BF=200000)
.MODEL DM1 D(IS=4.276E-12)
.MODEL DM2 D(IS=8e-16)
.ENDS LT1008
XU1 0 6 3 7 4 1 2 LT1008
V1 3 0 15 dc 1
V2 0 7 15 dc 1
V3 5 0 SINE(0 0.1 1k) ac 1
Rf1 6 4 50k
Rf2 0 0 1k
Ri 6 5 1k
C1 0 0 30p
C2 0 0 10p
C3 0 0 20p
* INSTRUCTIONS: Creative mode allows you to construct, simulate and implement a circuit in any way within the constraints of the hardware. You have been provided with every node necessary for constructing the circuit. Joining nodes will produce an error.
* IMPLEMENTATION NOTES: When this lab is opened, the relay controlling the power supply (Power - Port 1 Line 3 - ON) will switch ON. Once your circuit has been constructed, it will be checked against a set of possible valid implementations. If your circuit matches, it will be implemented on the hardware
* DIGOUTPUT0_PRE = 0 0 0 0 0 0 0 0
* DIGOUTPUT1_PRE = 0 0 0 1 0 0 0 0
* DIGOUTPUT0_POST = 1 0 0 0 0 0 0 0
* DIGOUTPUT1_POST = 0 0 0 1 0 0 0 0
* AOUTPUT0_PRE = 0.0
* AOUTPUT1_PRE = 0.0
* AOUTPUT0_POST = 0.0 
* AOUTPUT1_POST = 0.0 
* INDEX = Input*50,Output
.control
tran 5u 2m
run
print 50*v(5) v(4)
dc V1 15 15 0.1
dc V2 15 15 0.1
run
print v(1) v(2) v(3) v(4) v(5) v(6) v(7) v(8)
.endc

Questions.Title: Circuit Gain at 1kHz
Questions.Instructions: Check that your 1 kHz sinusoidal input voltage amplitude is below100mV and the output voltage is also sinusoidal (not slew ratelimited). Measure the gain.

Parts.Name: Part B - Effects of Frequency compensation

Sections.File: src/labs/1. Operational Amplifier/Part B - Effects of Frequency compensation/1. Compensation Capacitor Frequency Response.cir
Sections.Name: 1. Compensation Capacitor Frequency Response
Sections.Solution:
Frequency Response
.SUBCKT LT1008 3 2 7 4 6 1 8
* USE C=30 PF IN MAIN CIRCUIT (CA TO CB).
* INPUT
RC1 7 80 8842
RC2 7 90 8842
Q1 80 2 10 QM1
Q2 90 3 11 QM2
DDM1 2 3 DM2
DDM2 3 2 DM2
C1 80 90 8.66e-12
RE1 10 12 224.6
RE2 11 12 224.6
IEE 12 4 6e-6
RE 12 0 33330000
CE 12 0 1.579E-12
* INTERMEDIATE
GCM 0 8 12 0 2.841E-11
GA 8 0 80 90 1.131E-04
R2 8 0 100000
* EXTERNAL COMP CAP USED FOR C2 (SEE NOTE ABOVE).
GB 1 0 8 0 196
* OUTPUT
RO1 1 6 100
RO2 1 0 900
RC 17 0 6.802e-5
GC 0 17 6 0 14700
D1 1 17 DM1
D2 17 1 DM1
D3 6 13 DM2
D4 14 6 DM2
VC 7 13 1.774
VE 14 4 1.774
IP 7 4 0.000374
DSUB 4 7 DM2
.MODEL QM1 NPN(IS=8e-16 BF=66670)
.MODEL QM2 NPN(IS=8.009E-16 BF=200000)
.MODEL DM1 D(IS=4.276E-12)
.MODEL DM2 D(IS=8e-16)
.ENDS LT1008
XU1 0 6 3 7 4 1 2 LT1008
V1 3 0 15
V2 0 7 15
V3 5 0 ac 1 dc 0
R1 4 6 1k
R2 6 5 1k
C1 1 2 30p
C2 0 0 10p
C3 0 0 20p
C4 0 0 50p
C5 0 0 100p
* INSTRUCTIONS: Determine the 3dB Bandwidth, of this circuit, and then the frequency at which the gain falls to 0dB. Finally, plot the phase frequency response
* SIMULATION NOTES: Perform a frequency sweep of the circuit given. This will require configuring the virtual oscilloscope. Run the sweep up to 1MHz with decade time steps and 1 step per decade.
* IMPLEMENTATION NOTES: When this lab is opened, the relay controlling the power supply (Power - Port 1 Line 3 - ON) will switch ON, and the relay controlling the feedback resistor will switch to RF2 [unity gain] (S2 - Port 0 Line 1 ON). Upon successful completion of this lab, the Function generator switch will turn ON (S1 - Port 0 Line 0 ON). Capacitor 1 will Switch ON (S3 - Port 0 Line 2 - ON) All other capacitance switches (S4 - Port 0 Line 4 - OFF)(S5 - Port 0 Line 5 - OFF) will remain OFF
* DIGOUTPUT0_PRE = 0 1 1 0 0 0 0 0
* DIGOUTPUT1_PRE = 0 0 0 1 0 0 0 0
* DIGOUTPUT0_POST = 1 0 0 0 0 0 0 0
* DIGOUTPUT1_POST = 0 0 0 1 0 0 0 0
* AOUTPUT0_PRE = 0.0
* AOUTPUT1_PRE = 0.0
* AOUTPUT0_POST = 0.0 
* AOUTPUT1_POST = 0.0  
* INDEX = Output Voltage (V), Phase (Scaled)
.control
ac dec 10 0.1 100T
run
print 20*log10(v(4))
.endc

Sections.ImplementationNotes: When this lab is opened, the relay controlling the power supply (Power - Port 1 Line 3 - ON) will switch ON, and the relay controlling the feedback resistor will switch to RF1 [G=50] (S2 - Port 0 Line 1 OFF). Upon successful completion of this lab, the Function generator switch will turn ON (S1 - Port 0 Line 0 ON). The relay controlling capacitor 2 will switch ON (S4 - Port 0 Line 3 - ON). All other capacitance switches (S3 - Port 0 Line 2 - OFF)(S5 - Port 0 Line 4 - OFF) will remain OFF

Questions.Title: Circuit Gain at 1kHz
Questions.Instructions: Check that your 1 kHz sinusoidal input voltage amplitude is below100mV and the output voltage is also sinusoidal (not slew ratelimited). Measure the gain.

Sections.File: src/labs/2. Amplifier with Feedback/Part A - Differential Amplifier/0. Creative.cir
Sections.Name: 0. Creative
Sections.Solution:
*
.subckt lm741 Pin1_IN_$$PLUS$ Pin2_IN_$$MINUS$
+ Pin3_V_$$PLUS$ Pin4_V_$$MINUS$ Pin5_OUT
RU2$U4$R1 Pin4_V_$$MINUS$ U2$U4$OUT 144.0
RU2$U4$R2 U2$U4$OUT Pin3_V_$$PLUS$ 144.0
DU2$U4$D6 U2$U4$DRIVE_OUT U2$U4$V1_PIN_1 DG1 temp=27
.model DG1 D IS=1.0E-12
RU2$U4$R36 U2$U4$DRIVE_OUT Pin4_V_$$MINUS$ 2000000.0
RU2$U4$R38 Pin3_V_$$PLUS$ U2$U4$DRIVE_OUT 2000000.0
DU2$U4$D4 Pin3_V_$$PLUS$ U2$U4$D2_PIN_2 DG2
.model DG2 D
DU2$U4$D5 Pin4_V_$$MINUS$ U2$U4$D3_PIN_2 DG3
.model DG3 D BV=50.0
DU2$U4$D3 Pin3_V_$$PLUS$ U2$U4$D3_PIN_2 DG4
.model DG4 D
DU2$U4$D1 U2$U4$D1_PIN_1 U2$U4$DRIVE_OUT DG5 temp=27
.model DG5 D IS=1.0E-12
DU2$U4$D2 Pin4_V_$$MINUS$ U2$U4$D2_PIN_2 DG6
.model DG6 D BV=50.0
GU2$U4$B2$controlledSource U2$U4$D2_PIN_2 Pin4_V_$$MINUS$
+ VALUE={V(U2$U4$DRIVE_OUT, U2$U4$OUT) / (2.0 * 72.0)}
GU2$U4$G2$3 U2$U4$OUT Pin4_V_$$MINUS$ VALUE={-1.0 / (2.0 *
+ 72.0) * V(U2$U4$DRIVE_OUT, Pin4_V_$$MINUS$)}
VU2$U4$V2$1 U2$U4$OUT U2$U4$D1_PIN_1 1.3426910213823116
